<section id="coremap">
  <title id="map">map</title>

  <figure>
    <title>map</title>

    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="images/core/map.png" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>

  <para><filename>Map</filename> store the state of a mapping session. It is
  the <emphasis>Model</emphasis> part of the <emphasis>Model-View-Controller</emphasis>
  display design pattern.</para>

  <para>Multiple <emphasis>Context</emphasis> objects can be created using
  similar components in order to create widgets which share common components.
  For example. A display may contain two <filename>MapPanes</filename> which
  show the same area but use different basemaps. This would be achieved by
  building two <filename>Contexts</filename> which use the same
  <filename>BoundingBox</filename> but use different <filename>LayerLists</filename>.</para>

  <para><filename>Map</filename> is based on the <emphasis>OGC Web Map Context</emphasis>
  Specification which means <emphasis>map</emphasis> data could be stored as
  XML and imported into another <emphasis>Web Map Context</emphasis>
  Application.</para>
</section>